ignition-tools
------------------------------------------
Ignition tools provide the ign command line tool that accepts multiple
subcommands. Each subcommand is implemented in a plugin that belongs to a
specific Ignition project. For example, all the commands that start with ign
topic ... will be implemented by the Ignition Transport library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.203.gf78009cb1ccf
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  ruby-3.2.2-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  ignition-cmake-4.0.0-1bl2
  ninja-1.12.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/gazebosim/gz-tools

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/gazebosim/gz-tools/archive/refs/tags/gz-tools2_2.0.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ignition-tools-2.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ignition-tools-2.0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ignition-tools-2.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ignition-tools-2.0.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ignition-tools)
  /usr/bin/cyggz-tools2-backward-2.dll
  /usr/bin/gz
  /usr/lib/cmake/gz-tools2-all/gz-tools2-all-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/gz-tools2-all/gz-tools2-all-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/gz-tools2-all/gz-tools2-all-targets.cmake
  /usr/share/bash-completion/completions/gz
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ignition-tools.README
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/Changelog.md
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/README.md
  /usr/share/gz/gz.completion

